    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Once you reach 14th level, you learn the raise dead spell. Which counts as a warlock spell for you, but does not count against your number of warlock spells known.</p><p>If you have half of your hit points or less at the start of your turn, you regain hit points equal to either your Constitution modifier or Charisma modifier (your choice).</p><p>You do not gain this benefit if you are unconscious, or have 0 hit points.</p><p>Lastly, if you die, your patron will bring you back to life. They can cast @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.ua8QDrwxJod7JqWf]{Raise Dead} targeting only you from their realm across any distance, requiring no components. Once you come back to life in this way, you cannot do so again for 30 days (one month or in Materia 33 days).</p>",
